From: Adriel Santos <adriel@adriel.eu>
Subject: [PATCH] nss: an8855: tag_8021q port_bridge_leave (layered after 999-2757)

The NSS tag_8021q bridge fix wires .port_bridge_join to
dsa_tag_8021q_bridge_join() directly in the an8855.c files overlay. The
matching .port_bridge_leave cannot be expressed there: 999-2757 (add
an8855 v2p0p1 + netlink) already rewrites an8855_port_bridge_leave() on
top of the overlay to add regmap error handling, so editing the
overlay's copy makes that patch's hunk fail. Apply the tag_8021q leave
logic here instead, after 999-2757:

 - dsa_tag_8021q_bridge_leave() restores the port's standalone VID
   (SECURITY mode + PVID via .tag_8021q_vlan_add), reversing the
   cross-VLAN membership .port_bridge_join installed.
 - drop the forced MATRIX (VLAN-unaware) restore: a standalone tag_8021q
   port must keep classifying untagged ingress into its standalone VID
   so its CPU egress stays tagged for the conduit tagger to demux the
   source port.

NSS-only (ships in the nss/ overlay); the base MTK-tag build keeps
999-2757's plain error-handled leave.

Link: https://github.com/ADCDS/openwrt-xiaomi-ax3000t-rd03v2/issues/1
--- a/drivers/net/dsa/an8855.c
+++ b/drivers/net/dsa/an8855.c
@@ -523,22 +523,27 @@
 	struct an8855_priv *priv = ds->priv;
 	int ret;
 
+	/* tag_8021q: drop the shared bridge VID and restore this port's
+	 * standalone VID (its .tag_8021q_vlan_add PVID branch reprograms
+	 * SECURITY mode + standalone PVID), reversing the cross-VLAN
+	 * membership set up in .port_bridge_join so the port returns to
+	 * CPU-only isolation. Do NOT force MATRIX (VLAN-unaware) mode: a
+	 * standalone tag_8021q port must keep classifying untagged ingress
+	 * into its standalone VID so its CPU egress stays tagged for the
+	 * conduit tagger to demux the source port.
+	 */
+	dsa_tag_8021q_bridge_leave(ds, port, bridge);
+
 	ret = an8855_update_port_member(ds, port, bridge.dev, false);
 	if (ret) {
 		dev_err(priv->dev, "failed to update port member: %d\n", ret);
 		return;
 	}
 
-	/* When a port is removed from the bridge, the port would be set up
-	 * back to the default as is at initial boot which is a VLAN-unaware
-	 * port.
-	 */
-	ret = regmap_update_bits(priv->regmap, AN8855_PCR_P(port),
-			   AN8855_PORT_VLAN,
-			   FIELD_PREP(AN8855_PORT_VLAN,
-				      AN8855_PORT_MATRIX_MODE));
-	if (ret)
-		dev_err(priv->dev, "failed to update PCR reg: %d\n", ret);
+	/* DEBUG: show the shrunk bridge-VID membership on the console */
+	mutex_lock(&priv->reg_mutex);
+	an8855_tag_8021q_dump_vid(priv, dsa_tag_8021q_bridge_vid(bridge.num));
+	mutex_unlock(&priv->reg_mutex);
 }
 
 static int an8855_port_fdb_add(struct dsa_switch *ds, int port,
